Comment: This seems to promise a return to form. Bardem is a great actor. And the effects for him and his crew are really impressive and creepy. Tone also seems to be much darker, which is welcome (many forget the old movies had their share of horror moments, not just action/comedy). I like that it seems to be going back to the epic supernatural elements, like there were in the first three films. OST tried to backpedal on that, and it made it a visually uninteresting slog, after an entire trilogy of amazing sights and sounds. My fingers will be crossed for this one.

Title: Teaser Trailer: Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Men Tell No Tales
Comment:
There's a link to an old Easter Egg here, if you think about it.

DAVY: "Do you fear death?"
JACK: "You have no idea..."

Davy wasn't death; he simply transported the dead at sea to an eternal resting place (which later became more of a prison due to Davy's corruption and inability to keep doing his job). Davy bargained with men to delay their meeting with "Death".

Captain Salazar may, in fact, be Death (or his errand boy) coming for Jack. Given how many people have grudges with Sparrow, and how many stories surround him, it's quite possible he's been alive for several centuries eluding Death.

Title: Teaser Trailer: Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Men Tell No Tales
Comment: Ok so as I am watching this figure walk through the ship cutting down people, my immeadiate thought was that Will Turner had finally lost his mind and gone down the same road davey jones did, hunting down ships to add to his ranks. His face being hidden his long flowing hair always hiding him. leaving us to wonder. But then they show what must obviously be Will Turners son behind bars...on a british naval ship... And I then think, OH this isn't a monsterous attack, This is William coming to rescue his son. And as the music plays in a hauntingly similar fashion to davey jones theme, the figure walks down the steps and the look on that kids face, as though hes seeing someone he never expected to see.... and then bam the sword into the sparrow flyer... I was waiting for williams face to show behind it. But NO! For a split second we see what appears to be wills father bootstrape bill, and what looks like the sea life growth on his face returned. Its only when he steps into the light and says his name do we realize... this is someone new and this is a whole different game now. THATS how you do a mother f*cking trailer!

Title: Teaser Trailer: Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Men Tell No Tales
Comment:
I'm so exited for Pirates Of The Caribbean 576. Seriously, just give up. Nobody likes this shitty series. The first film was loads of fun, the second and third made no goddamn sense and the fourth was just a shitty action movie. You're flogging a horse so dead its skeleton has decomposed. Realistically, many people will pay to see it, but that's just because they loved the first film and over-optimistically hope for a return to form, which will probably never happen. You'll get terrible reviews and you'll try again every five years, further embarrassing Disney and shitting all over the first film. It's seriously difficult to enjoy the first film knowing it's part of the same series as three (and probably now four) utter pieces of shit. Just use your budget to make a great original film. You'll probably get the same amount of money either way, but this way you'll have integrity. If you absolutely must 
turn this series into James Bond, just understand why everyone loves the first film. It's not because of its action, its fantasy, its deep and complex characters, or its many deep and complex subplots. It's simply because it's loads of fun. When you try to make a POTC film driven by those former elements, you epically fail. Please stop trying to be like Star Wars.

So it's been 10 years since Will became Captain. That means he's allowed to visit land for one day. Does this mean he'll visit Elizabeth? His son? Is that boy in the trailer his son? So much I want to know...

 I need to see this movie NOW.

Title: Teaser Trailer: Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Men Tell No Tales
Comment:
My thoughts:
Javier Bardem is amazing actor, I am glad he was given a different look-he fits in with this franchise, but is not too similar to the skeletons, zombies, or Davey Jone's crew.
With the time taken into making this film, along with the return of characters and those related, it is clear this film will have a good amount going on. Not simply a race to a fountain with no real super-natural force beside one big scene (the mermaids) and a magic sword/ship. This is going to be "death in his wake" and battle time, for one reason or another. Stronger acting, not the very mellow, stand in blackbeard we got in 4. Ghosts, how do you stop them, hmmmm? The mood is also far more the tone of 1, 2, and 3.
In conclusion, from this, I believe this franchised has worked to learn, instead of simply hoping for another hit. I expect better 3D hopefully (don't be cheap disney) as well.

Title: Teaser Trailer: Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Men Tell No Tales
Comment:
_Pirates of the Caribbean_ died with the second film.  They added too much supernatural crap and the threat/suspense of any character really dying.....well, died.
They tried to scale back a bit with the forth film and attempted to recreate a bit of the charm lost in _Curse of the Black Pearl_ (instead of the over-bloated complexity of 2 & 3).  It came out as "meh" and simply uninteresting.

Based on the teaser, this film looks no different.  Another supernatural underdead pirate guy with his "magic" crew is after Jack Sparrow and wants to kill him....supernaturally.  Wow, what a shock. -__-
(I was really really hoping that this teaser was Will Turner doing his work as Davy Jones but nope!)
